Jiangxi will train 10,000 rural primary school music, physical education and fine arts teachers within 3 years.
In order to enhance the ability to guarantee the shortage of subject teachers and achieve equal development of rural compulsory education, Jiangxi Province has planned to spend 3 years from 2016 to train 10,000 qualified music, art, and physical education teachers in each of the rural (township and below) primary schools in the province.
It is understood that the training targets are teachers in Jiangxi's rural primary schools under the age of 45 with a basic knowledge of music, art, and physical education or talent, and who are capable of teaching other subjects besides music, art, and physical education.
Through training, they will master the basic knowledge and teaching skills of music, physical education and fine arts, update their teaching ideas and concepts, master modern teaching methods, improve their subject teaching ability, activity design ability, campus cultural ability and self-development ability, and build a team of music, physical education and fine arts teachers with multiple capabilities to alleviate the shortage of rural music, physical education and fine arts teachers.
In order to ensure the quality and effectiveness of the training, Jiangxi also plans to train 1 person in music, art, and physical education for 100 county (city, district) primary schools in the province, a total of 300 training participants, comprehensively enhancing their teaching demonstration leading ability, teaching research and activity design organization ability, training ability, and network research training workshop construction ability, playing the role of teaching, demonstrating, guiding, and supervising.